r21/news02.php, \r\nhttp://ccafs.cgiar.org/blog/learning-platform-climate-smart-agriculture-getting-increased-attention, \r\nhttp://ccafs.cgiar.org/blog/Future-drivers-food-security-climate-adaptation-South-Asia-explored%20', '', '8', '12', '2012', '2014-02-28 15:10:32'), ('1418', null, null, '1850', 'http://ccafs.cgiar.org/blog/hundreds-elected-women-rural-bihar-get-trained-climate-change-and-food-security', '', '8', '13', '2012', '2014-02-28 15:10:32'), ('1419', null, null, '1', 'http://ccafs.cgiar.org/blog/learning-platform-climate-smart-agriculture-getting-increased-attention', '', '8', '16', '2012', '2014-02-28 15:10:32'), ('1420', null, null, '1', '', '', '8', '27', '2012', '2014-02-28 15:10:32'), ('1421', null, null, '', '', '', '8', '28', '2012', '2014-02-28 15:10:32'), ('1422', null, null, '', '', '', '8', '29', '2012', '2014-02-28 15:10:32'), ('1423', null, null, '100', '', '', '8', '32', '2012', '2014-02-28 15:10:32'), ('1424', null, null, '2', 'High impact paper by Jarvis, A. et al. 2012. Is Cassava the Answer to African Climate Change Adaptation? \r\n\r\n* Uptake in the popular press was tremendous, including live radio interviews.  The story appeared in BBC, Scientific American, NBS, MSN, and in important daily papers form across the globe.  The stories made reference to cassava as a Rambo Root.Beyond media impact, the Rambo Root phrase is currently being used by the Global Cassava partnership (funded by the Gates Foundation) as the primary communications instrument for attracting more attention to the crop.  The significant exposure has resulted in renewed attention being given to Cassava as an orphan crop with significant potential to contribute to adaptation.  Through communications, the primary message from the paper has significantly impacted on increased funding investment, and development attention being given to cassava.\r\n\r\n* Participatory social return on investment (PSROI) framework \r\n\r\n1) PAPER: Is Cassava the Answer to African Clima