ite will be re-designed in 2014), T4.2: Dorward work on use of weather forecasts\r\nUniversity of Cape Town work on use of weather forecasts', null, '5', '17', '2013', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2395', 'T4.3: 20, T4.2: 2', null, 'T4.1: 0, T4.3: 20, T4.2: 2', 'T4.3: http://globalfutures.cgiar.org/files/2014/06/Two_pager-10-31.pdf\r\n\r\nhttp://www.oecd.org/officialdocuments/publicdisplaydocumentpdf/?cote=COM/TAD/CA/ENV/EPOC%282013%2919/FINAL&docLanguage=En\r\n\r\n(in collaboration with PIM), T4.2: PICSA and UCT support of farmer decision making processes', 'T4.3: 16 virtual technologies were analyzed under no climate change and with climate change for the Global Futures promising technology policy brief\r\n4 irrigation technology scenarios were analyzed under climate change and no climate change for the OECD report, T4.2: -', '5', '17', '2014', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2396', 'T4.1: 0, T4.3: 10, T4.2: 0', '0', '0', '', 'T4.3 is now largely reported under IFPRI', '5', '17', '2015', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2397', null, null, 'T4.1: 0', null, null, '5', '18', '2012', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2398', null, null, 'T4.3: 0, T4.2: 100', 'T4.2: Dorward work\r\nUCT work', null, '5', '18', '2013', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2399', 'T4.3: 0, T4.2: 100', null, 'T4.1: 0, T4.2: 50', 'T4.2: both activities have elements of targeting women, but not fully', 'T4.2: -', '5', '18', '2014', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2400', 'T4.1: 0, T4.2: 0', '0', '0', '', '', '5', '18', '2015', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2401', null, null, 'T4.1: 0', null, null, '5', '19', '2012', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2402', null, null, 'T4.3: 0, T4.2: 0', null, null, '5', '19', '2013', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2403', 'T4.3: 0, T4.2: 50', null, 'T4.1: 0, T4.2: 50', 'T4.2: PICSA', 'T4.2: -', '5', '19', '2014', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2404', 'T4.1: 0, T4.2: 0', '0', '0', '', '', '5', '19', '2015', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2405', null, null, 'T4.1: 0', null, null, '5', '20', '2012', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2406', 'T4.1: 0', null, 'T4.3: 0, T4.2: 0', null, null, '5', '20', '2013', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2407', 'T4.3: 0, T4.2: 0', null, 'T4.1: 0, T4.2: 0', null, null, '5', '20', '2014', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2408', 'T4.2: 0, T4.1: 0', '3', '3', 'CCSL has worked with the Bolsa Floresta program of the Amazonas Sustainable Foundation that has piloted the CCSL M&E Framework (https://ccafs.cgiar.org/publications/monitoring-and-evaluating-social-learning-framework-cross-initiative-application#.VvzXn3AStKk) with 10 different projects in 10 different communities. These communities are working with FAS to address NRM issues in different ecosystems in the Brazilian Amazon including local lakes (fishing) and forests (logging). A second program piloting the framework is the Potato Park in Peru (a CIP program). This program works with potato farmers. These are examples of the ecosystems for which CCSL has helped locally-operating programs to identify feasible approaches for improving ecosystem services and establish positive incentives; however, we do not provide recommendations directly - instead we promote a process for achieving better and more sustainable outcomes.', '', '5', '20', '2015', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2409', null, null, 'T4.1: 0', null, null, '5', '21', '2012', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2410', 'T4.1: 0', null, 'T4.3: 0, T4.2: 0', null, null, '5', '21', '2013', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2411', 'T4.3: 0, T4.2: 0', null, 'T4.1: 0, T4.2: 0', null, null, '5', '21', '2014', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2412', 'T4.2: 10000, T4.1: 0', '200000', '175000', 'PICSA is being implemented in new areas of existing countries (Tanzania, Ghana) where it has already been used, and in further countries in 2016. For example by 2020 it is planned that it will be used in all districts in Rwanda under a USAID funded and CCAFS run project that has just started.\r\n\r\nhttps://ccafs.cgiar.org/publications/participatory-integrated-climate-services-agriculture-picsa-field-manual; https://www.dropbox.com/sh/2y50js51msadcfr/AAAgfSo_jdV3j1Xr8oyLIYjAa?dl=0', 'M&E of the PICSA program in Ghana showed that, on average, each farmer trained shared knowledge with five other farmers, thereby creating a ripple effect that is much larger than we had anticipated in our original target.', '5', '21', '2015', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2413', null, null, 'T4.1: 0', null, null, '5', '22', '2012', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2414', 'T4.1: 0', null, 'T4.3: 0, T4.2: 1', 'T4.2: Dorward tool', null, '5', '22', '2013', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2415', 'T4.3: 0, T4.2: 1', null, 'T4.1: 0, T4.2: 1', 'T4.2: picsa', null, '5', '22', '2014', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2416', 'T4.2: 0, T4.1: 0', '1', '1', 'https://ccafs.cgiar.org/publications/participatory-integrated-climate-services-agriculture-picsa-field-manual', '', '5', '22', '2015', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2417', null, null, 'T4.1: 0', null, null, '5', '23', '2012', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2418', 'T4.1: 0', null, 'T4.3: 0, T4.2: 0', null, null, '5', '23', '2013', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2419', 'T4.3: 0, T4.2: 0', null, 'T4.1: 0, T4.2: 1', 'T4.2: picsa', null, '5', '23', '2014', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2420', 'T4.2: 3, T4.1: 0', '6', '6', 'CCSL: Amazon, Peru altiplano\r\nPICSA:  Malawi, Tanzania X2, Northern Ghana', '', '5', '23', '2015', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2421', null, null, 'T4.1: 0', null, null, '5', '24', '2012', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2422', 'T4.1: 0', null, 'T4.3: 0, T4.2: 0', null, null, '5', '24', '2013', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2423', 'T4.3: 0, T4.2: 0', null, 'T4.1: 0, T4.2: 0', null, null, '5', '24', '2014', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2424', 'T4.2: 0, T4.1: 0', '100', '100', 'CCSL and PICSA promote equality between men and women', '', '5', '24', '2015', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2425', null, null, 'T4.1: 0', null, null, '5', '25', '2012', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2426', 'T4.1: 0', null, 'T4.3: 0, T4.2: 0', null, null, '5', '25', '2013', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2427', 'T4.3: 0, T4.2: 0', null, 'T4.1: 5