42'), ('2438', 'T4.1: 0', null, 'T4.3: 29, T4.2: 0', 'T4.3: As part of the regional launch process for the African Agriculture and Climate Change Series, the three books (covering 29 countries in SSA) were discussed with national stakeholders around three major regional events:\r\n\r\n-Launch of \"West African Agriculture and Climate Change\" at the “Regional Workshop to Mainstream Climate Change in the West Africa Agricultural Productivity Programme,”organized by CORAF/WECARD, April 2, Niamey, Niger. \r\n- Launch of \"Southern African Agriculture and Climate Change\" in Maseru, Lesotho in September 2013, at the FANRPAN High-Level Food Security Multi-Stakeholder Policy Dialogue.\r\n- Publication of the special edition Kenya chapter in September 2013 to support initiatives by CCAFS in the East Africa region.\r\n- Launch of \"East African Agriculture and Climate Change\" in Bujumbura, Burundi in December 2013 at ASARECA\'s Second Annual General Assembly. The meeting was attended by several African Ministers of Agriculture. \r\n\r\nAdditionally, as documented in the \"4.3 outcomes\" and in the outcome indicators, in four countries (Ghana, Kenya, Nigeria and Liberia), key policy conclusions from the project have been presented for public/stakeholder consultation, in various forms of meetings.', null, '5', '28', '2013', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2439', 'T4.3: 0, T4.2: 0', null, 'T4.1: 4, T4.2: 4', 'T4.1: Description: Policies in Cambodia, Bangladesh, Colombia and Honduras. see the scenarios case study report for details: https://www.dropbox.com/s/ldeumebx8hrdrj6/Case%20study%20CCAFS%20scenario-guided%20policy%20research%202014.docx?dl=0, T4.2: Policies in Cambodia, Bangladesh, Colombia and Honduras. see the scenarios case study report for details: https://www.dropbox.com/s/ldeumebx8hrdrj6/Case%20study%20CCAFS%20scenario-guided%20policy%20research%202014.docx?dl=0', null, '5', '28', '2014', '2016-02-11 22:49:42'), ('2440', 'T4.2: 3, T4.1: 0', '5', '11', 'https://www.dropb