rs. Information materials were produced considering local contexts.', 'Extension programs that specifically target women groups will be developed.', 'current SCA specific extension services that directly involve women are on wider promotion of homegardening and small livestock raising.', '1', '2015-11-06 00:55:32', '871', '871', ''), ('171', '55', '171', '2015', '- Vulnerability assessments will include analysis of traditional coping mechanisms.\r\n- CSA options and CBA strategies will be developed based on identified needs and will be built on existing traditional coping mechanisms.', '14 Relevant existing (on-site and in nearby localities) CSA technologies/strategies identified as key to increasing adaptive capacities of farmers in research site: homegardening, livestock raising, intercropping, forestry, farm economic, agroforestry, landscape, soil improvement, water harvest & management, weather forecast, coffee intercropping, coastal bioshields, community seed bank, media advocacy, coffee rejuvenation', 'Gender differentiated analysis of vulnerabilities will provide basis for drawing up gender-sensitive adaptation strategies.', 'Both PH & VN research sites are registering 2 key CSA practices that are most relevant to women members of the community: homegarden improvement and livestock raising. Participation  is also highest in community-level activities (training, workshop, field days, media days, demonstrations) concerning these 2 CSA practices.', '1', '2015-11-06 00:55:32', '871', '871', ''), ('172', '55', '172', '2015', 'Proof-of-concept sites establishment will incorporate analysis of its implications to local government processes.', 'aside from developing impact sites, proof-of-concept site establishment with direct implication to governance still in frameworks and concept level.', 'Vulnerability assessments, stakeholder analysis and institutional mapping will provide analysis for drawing up strategies to increase participation of women to local government 