, '1', '2015-11-06 08:20:26', '108', '108', ''), ('197', '54', '175', '2016', 'The initial project phase will be based on well-established CSA practices derived from previous projects as entry points. Thus, the Project can directly move towards CSA certification schemes and new agri-business modelsto promote and mainstream CSA adoption.', null, 'It is important to include in the CSV portfolio CSA activities that are community-based in nature, and can contribute to increasing resilience of women and poorer households in the village who may not be able to directly participate in the CSA pilot activities due to lack of time/ resources.', null, '1', '2015-11-06 08:20:26', '108', '108', ''), ('198', '54', '174', '2016', 'The project works closely with with an ICT expert (funded thorugh a bilateral grant) who develops a descision support tool for rice rpoduction based on mobile phone technology. This tool on applying CSA technologies will be shared  with farmers, extension services, seed suppliers, local governments etc.', null, 'The knowledge management of this project will fully incorporate gender and social differenciation as a main feature of compiling and structuring information.', null, '1', '2015-11-06 08:20:26', '108', '108', ''), ('199', '54', '171', '2016', 'The participatory approach of this project will ensure to meet the needs of farmers and enhance productivity. In the next level, the activities will improve adaptive capacity, food security and social equity at village scale while the upscaling will follow suit beyond 2016.', null, 'Capacity building for CSA technologies and practices in the 4 CSVs will target women and poorer households in the village and facilitate their engagement in the scale out.', null, '0', '2015-11-06 08:20:26', '108', '108', ''), ('200', '54', '172', '2016', 'The CSVs will function as catalysts for scaling of CSA technologies and thus, create an enabling environment within the respective province. the project approach includes support tools for CSA prioritization as a means for wide scale adoption,', null, 'Capacity building for CSA technologies and practices in the 4 CSVs will target women and poorer households in the village and facilitate their engagement in the scale out.', null, '1', '2015-11-06 08:20:26', '108', '108', '');
