nd active involvement of women/men farmers in national policy processes assesed. National decision makers made some efforts to take differences into consideration in policy/law formulation.', '1', '2015-11-18 12:15:25', '68', '68', ''), ('776', '66', '178', '2015', '', 'We sponsored/organized interactions between African Union Commission and key national level actors (engaged, cumulatively,  in climate change adaptation, genetic resource conservation and sustainable use, and domestication of multilateral environmental agreements) from a number of African countries. This culminated in a decision that AU Commission/CCAFS will develop policy/guidelines in 2016/17.', '', 'The policy/guidelines will, when drafted, highlight the importance of social inclusion and provide examples for how national programs can put inclusive systems in place to allow women and men, and socially marginalized people within countries, to take advantage of the ITPGRFA for climate change adaptation.', '1', '2015-11-18 12:15:25', '68', '68', ''), ('777', '66', '176', '2016', 'National partners engage in policy analysis and development, most of which to be finished in 2017 and 2018', null, 'State recognition of local community rights to participate in decision making regarding the conservation and exploitation of genetic resources. Local community develop access and benefit sharing protocols. Women included in local community committees to consider access applications.', null, '1', '2015-11-18 12:15:25', '68', '68', ''), ('778', '66', '178', '2016', 'AU Commission works with Bioversity on guidelines on implementing ABS laws to support climate change adaptation based on consultations with national and local actors.', null, 'The guidelines will encourage African AU member states to put systems in place reflecting recognition of the right of local communities -- and wormen within those communities -- to participate in decision making concerning access to and management of genetic diversity and sharing benefits associated with their use by others.', null, '1', '2015-11-18 12:15:25', '68', '68', ''), ('779', '66', '176', '2017', '', null, '', null, '0', '2015-11-18 12:15:25', '68', '68', ''), ('780', '66', '178', '2017', '', null, '', null, '0', '2015-11-18 12:15:25', '68', '68', ''), ('781', '45', '48', '2019', '', null, '', null, '1', '2015-11-18 17:21:57', '98', '98', ''), ('782', '45', '48', '2015', '', '- In 2015 we were in the process of designing climate smart insurance products. We have implemented a survey and focus group discussions to understand major risks and attitudes toward insurance products. We are working with collaborators to analyze satellite data to help design insurance products', '', 'None gender and social inclusion dimension at this early stage of the project', '1', '2015-11-18 17:21:57', '98', '98', ''), ('783', '45', '48', '2016', '- Weather insurance products with the potential to encourage CSA technologies adoption will be designed and tested at small scale pilots in Haryana and Punjab, India\r\n- Engagement of government officials, farmers associations and insurance industry with project evolution aiming at preparing the way for future scaling up', null, '- As we design weather insurance products and test them we will pay attention to gender differences in take-up, potential impact, marketing channels and CSA technology adoption.', null, '1', '2015-11-18 17:21:57', '98', '98', ''), ('784', '45', '48', '2017', '', null, '', null, '0', '2015-11-18 17:21:57', '98', '98', ''), ('785', '67', '176', '2019', '', null, '', null, '1', '2015-11-19 02:08:10', '153', '153', ''), ('786', '67', '178', '2019', '', null, '', null, '1', '2015-11-19 02:08:10', '153', '153', ''), ('787', '67', '179', '2019', '', null, '', null, '1', '2015-11-19 02:08:10', '153', '153', ''), ('788', '67', '176', '2015', '', 'Scenarios developed, networks established, reports completed (noting the last one is still in production)', '', 'Gendered dimensions were included 