g CCAFS science', 'Increased participation among rural target women, from 30% in 2017, to at least 43% based on AIP membership and decision making in initiated CSA broad activities.', '2017', '39', '13', '66', null, null, null, '0', '2015-11-12 12:06:15', '95', '95', ''), ('7593', '11', '3 AIPs comprising of active CBOs, private businesses and extension are leading CSA testing, feedback and establishing business-focused activities to support the process.  These AIPs are receiving continuing support from NARIS in the three countries (KALRO, NARO, SARI), CRS, and three national NGOs (CIDI, EFA, AGMARK). New partnerships that enable participatory testing are further strengthened.', 'At least 30% of farmers participating in the CSA evaluation, receiving CSA portfolio advice, and actively participating in Agricultural Innovation Platforms are women and youth.', '2017', '39', '14', '67', null, null, null, '0', '2015-11-12 12:06:15', '95', '95', ''), ('7594', '', '', '', '2019', '203', '38', '69', null, null, null, '1', '2015-11-12 12:20:57', '910', '910', ''), ('7595', null, null, null, '2015', '203', '38', '69', null, null, null, '1', '2015-11-12 12:20:57', '910', '910', ''), ('7596', '', '', '', '2016', '203', '38', '69', null, null, null, '1', '2015-11-12 12:20:57', '910', '910', ''), ('7597', '', '', '', '2017', '203', '38', '69', null, null, null, '1', '2015-11-12 12:20:57', '910', '910', ''), ('7598', null, '', null, '2019', '142', '13', '53', null, null, null, '1', '2015-11-12 13:49:38', '271', '271', ''), ('7599', '3', null, null, '2015', '142', '13', '53', '3.00', 'Shade tree advise takes into considerations needs of the farmer, including specific needs of women farmers.', 'The shade tree advise is being used by 1 organisation in Uganda (Hans R. Neumann Stiftung) and 2 organisations in Ghana (Kuapa Kokoo and Agro-Eco)', '1', '2015-11-12 13:49:38', '271', '271', ''), ('7600', '2', 'Coffee and Climate Initiative and Rainforest Alliance will use the framework and toolboxes', 'Gender entry-points are taken into consideration in framework and toolbox', '2016', '142', '13', '53', null, null, null, '1', '2015-11-12 13:49:38', '271', '271', ''), ('7601', '', '', '', '2017', '142', '13', '53', null, null, null, '0', '2015-11-12 13:49:38', '271', '271', ''), ('7602', '2', null, null, '2015', '125', '13', '13', '2.00', '- GSI contributed the module on Gender and Stakeholder Involvement based on CCAFS case studies and research to the World Bank CSA 101 website (to be completed in 2016). \r\n- Gender and Inclusion Toolkit disseminated widely. \r\n- Collaborated with FAO on a Practice Brief on Gender and CSA to be published in early 2016. \r\n- Contributed substantially to two chapters in the World Bank-IFAD-FAO Module on Gender and CSA published in 2015. \r\n- Contribution of chapter on analysis of global trends in gender and S&E in the UNESCO Science Report.', 'Public institutions - At least two of FAO, WB, IFAD will include CCAFS research and tools in their tools and publications supporting CSA.', '1', '2015-11-12 15:14:49', '842', '294', ''), ('7603', '6', '2 initiatives incorporating GSI (e.g. testing HH methodologies) will be shared with national and subnational development initiatives and lessons learned shared with CSA networks, across CCAFS regions and at the global level. 4 international agencies will continue to use CCAFS GSI tools – Toolbox, case studies, new approaches and tools arising from a gendered HH approach and building from evidence from Gender HH survey (e.g. FAO, CARE, IFAD, World Bank). A pillar on GSI will be developed for the CSA compendium. Gender-sensitive CSA approaches will also be shared through the  CCAFS website, social media, journal articles, meetings and international fora.', 'GSI focuses 100% on gender and social inclusion', '2016', '125', '13', '13', null, null, null, '1', '2015-11-12 15:14:49', '842', '294', ''), ('7604', '', '', '', '2017', '125', '13', '13', null, null, null, '0', '2015-11-12 15:1